h1. Overview

h2. The Problem

We were shipping logs to Dynatrace without clear control or cost optimization. This meant:
- Uncontrolled log ingestion causing unexpected costs
- No clear separation between platform and application logs
- Inconsistent configuration across AKS clusters and VMs
- Application teams had no way to manage their own logs

h2. The Solution

We've implemented a cost-optimized approach where:
- By default, only pre-approved platform logs are shipped
- Application teams can opt-in to ship their own logs
- The approach is consistent across AKS and VMs
- Every log shipping decision is tracked and auditable

h2. Expected Benefits

- 80-90% reduction in unexpected log costs
- Application teams have full control and autonomy
- Clear audit trail of what logs are being shipped
- Easy to disable if logs are no longer needed

---

h1. How It Works

h2. The Core Principle: Default Deny, Explicit Opt-in

Think of it like this:
- By default, no application logs are sent to Dynatrace
- We only ship logs that the operations team has pre-approved as essential
- If your team needs logs in Dynatrace, you explicitly enable them
- You control which logs get shipped and can disable anytime

{info}
Platform logs (kernel events, security logs, OneAgent diagnostics) are automatically shipped by default. These are essential for monitoring and compliance. You don't need to do anything to get these.
{info}

