h1. Cost Management

h2. How Costs Work

We pay Dynatrace based on how much log data we ingest. Right now, we're paying roughly 2 cents per GB of logs.

h2. Cost Scenarios

|Scenario|Daily Volume|Monthly Cost|
|Platform logs only (everyone gets this)|20 GB per day|400 EUR|
|Plus 1 application opted-in|25 GB per day|500 EUR|
|Plus 5 applications opted-in|35 GB per day|700 EUR|

So if you opt-in one application with moderate logging, expect to add about 100 EUR per month to our Dynatrace bill.

h2. Ways to Keep Costs Down

If you need to ship logs but want to minimize costs, try these approaches:

*Only ship error logs*
Instead of shipping all logs, only ship ERROR and WARNING level logs. This cuts volume by 50-80%.

{code:language=yaml}
# For AKS
dynatrace.com/log-level: "WARN,ERROR"
{code}

*Sample your logs*
Ship only 50% or 25% of your logs. Useful for high-volume applications.

{code:language=yaml}
# For AKS - only ship 50% of logs
dynatrace.com/log-sampling: "50"
{code}

*Review quarterly*
Every 3 months, look at which applications have logs being shipped. Turn off any that you're no longer actively using.

