h1. Troubleshooting

h2. My logs aren't showing up in Dynatrace

First, wait 5 minutes after enabling. Logs don't appear instantly.

*For AKS*

Check that the annotation was applied correctly:

{code:language=bash}
kubectl get pod YOUR_POD_NAME -o jsonpath='{.metadata.annotations.dynatrace\.com/log-shipping}'
{code}

You should see "true". If you see nothing or "false", the annotation wasn't applied properly.

Check that OneAgent is running:

{code:language=bash}
kubectl get pods -n dynatrace | grep oneagent
{code}

You should see one oneagent pod per node.

*For Linux VMs*

Check that the symlink exists and works:

{code:language=bash}
ls -la /opt/dynatrace/logshipping/applications/my-app/
{code}

You should see symlinks to your log files.

Check that OneAgent is running:

{code:language=bash}
systemctl status dynatrace-oneagent
{code}

*For Windows VMs*

Check that the files exist:

{code:language=powershell}
Get-ChildItem "C:\Dynatrace\LogShipping\Applications\MyApp\"
{code}

You should see your log files.

Check that OneAgent is running:

{code:language=powershell}
Get-Service "Dynatrace OneAgent"
{code}

*If still not working*

1. Make sure your log files actually have content
2. Make sure OneAgent can read the log files (check file permissions)
3. Check the OneAgent logs for errors
4. Contact the platform team (see Support section below)

h2. I'm getting too many logs / costs are too high

*Reduce to error logs only*

Ship only ERROR and CRITICAL level logs instead of all logs.

*Enable sampling*

Ship only a percentage of your logs. For example, ship 25% instead of 100%.

*Disable for now*

If you don't need the logs right now, disable them and turn them back on later when needed.

h2. Permission denied error

*For Linux*

{code:language=bash}
sudo chown dynatrace:dynatrace /opt/dynatrace/logshipping/applications/my-app
sudo chmod 755 /opt/dynatrace/logshipping/applications/my-app
{code}

*For Windows*

{code:language=powershell}
$acl = Get-Acl "C:\Dynatrace\LogShipping\Applications\MyApp"
$rule = New-Object System.Security.AccessControl.FileSystemAccessRule("NT SERVICE\Dynatrace OneAgent","Read","ContainerInherit,ObjectInherit","None","Allow")
$acl.AddAccessRule($rule)
Set-Acl -Path "C:\Dynatrace\LogShipping\Applications\MyApp" -AclObject $acl
{code}

