h1. Common Questions

h2. How long does it take for logs to appear after I enable?

Usually 5 minutes. If it takes longer, check the troubleshooting section.

h2. Can I change which logs get shipped without restarting my application?

Yes. On VMs, you can create or remove symlinks anytime. On AKS, you need to redeploy your pod with updated annotations. The redeploy uses rolling updates, so there's no downtime.

h2. What if my logs contain sensitive data?

Use the log level filter to exclude debug logs, or use the exclude patterns to filter out specific lines. If you have concerns, contact the security team.

h2. Can I use this on non-production environments?

Yes, the same approach works for dev and test environments.

h2. Can I see my cost impact?

Yes, go to the Dynatrace cost dashboard. You can see exactly how much log data your applications are ingesting.

h2. What if I don't want any of my logs in Dynatrace?

That's fine. Don't add the annotation or symlink. Only platform logs will be shipped.

h2. Who do I contact if I have problems?

Reach out to the platform team. You can find us on Slack at #platform-ops or email platform-ops@example.com.

